The paper deals with the problem of sampling from the lattice Gaussian distribution, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed algorithm is a Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) algorithm, which is a common technique in computer science for generating samples from complex distributions, and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the convergence properties of the Markov chain arising from the algorithm, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.LG) and control theory (cs.SY).
